data.title: Victoria springs upset at Schools day two
data.meta_description: Victoria springs upset at Schools day two
data.text:
The second day of the Australian Schools Rugby Championship is in the books and the contenders have emerged.

Both NSW sides remain undefeated after convincing wins against ACT (NSW I) and WA (NSW II), while Queensland I kept Combined States scoreless in their clash.

Victoria caused the upset of the tournament to date in their clash with QLD II, keeping the Queenslanders winless through their first two starts.

The third and final pool matches will be played Thursday, with finals day on Saturday.
